<br>
<br>
<br>
This Charter is a standard guideline. If there are no rules posted in a raid’s signup sheet, these are the rules that will be adhered to. If there is a contradiction between these rules and the rules stated on a signup post, the signup post will take precedence.<br>
<br>
<br>
Part 1 - Conduct<br>
<br>
1) All raiders are to follow the explicit instructions of the Raid Leader. His/her orders are the be all end all, and failure to comply will result in being asked to leave, and if serious enough, a ban from all future Violent Harvest sponsored raids.<br>
<br>
2) &quot;Peeking&quot; at drops is strictly forbidden, unless you are told to do so by the loot roller or raid leader. <br>
<br>
3) If there are any problems/questions, ask your Group Leader, do not send tells to the Raid Leader or ask in the raid chat channel. If a group leader does not have the answer, they may send the raid Leader a tell.<br>
<br>
4) Group Leaders are to loot all corpses that are the result of that group's kill.<br>
<br>
5) If a raider is late for the appointed meeting time, he/she will be replaced. A meeting time is set for a reason, and it is considered disrespectful to Violent Harvest if you are late.<br>
<br>
6) All raiders are to check in by /tell with their Group Leader for the raid once they are online and ready to go. This means, you must check the list, and know who your leader will be before raid day. Group Leaders are responsible for giving group status to the Raid Leader for replacements. Replacements check in with Raid Leader by /tell to be placed as necessary. This rule is to minimize the stress on the raid leader, and to allow him to handle all necessary parts without having a thousand tells of who is checking in.<br>
<br>
7) Violent Harvest will supply all reagents for a raid either before or after the raid. It is the raider's responsibility to make sure that they are reimbursed, or given reagents before the raid.<br>
<br>
 Once the Raid Leader has decided that the raid is over, and the people who wish to leave do so, Violent Harvest takes no responsibility for any raiders who stay after that, and Violent Harvest waives all rights to the above-mentioned rules.<br>
<br>
9) All raiders will assist on the Main Assist, or the Secondary Assist as the situation requires. All raiders should have a hot key for the two assists.<br>
<br>
10) The designated raid channel is reserved for Raid officials only.<br>
<br>
<br>
Part 2 - Loot<br>
<br>
1) All items are Can and Will Use as primary gear. If there is no one on the raid who can use an item, it is forfeited to the Violent Harvest's guild vault.<br>
<br>
2) All cash gems, and coin are claimed by Violent Harvest's guild vault.<br>
<br>
3) Spells are to be awarded on a Can and Will Use basis. There will be no distinction between those who can currently scribe the spell and those who cannot. Any unclaimed spells are to go to the guild vault.<br>
<br>
4) Non-Armor Quest pieces are Can and Will Use, with priority given to people of sufficient level to complete the quest. These rolls are separate from all other types of rolls.<br>
<br>
5) Last Piece rule is in effect if inspected before the raid. This is Last Piece of a FULL set of one specific armor type, not Last usable or desired piece of armor. <br>
<br>
6) Breastplate rolls are separate from other armor rolls. Violent Harvest does not distinguish between Class/Quest armour pieces and other armour types in either the Breastplate or other armor category.<br>
<br>
7) Weapons are separate from armor rolls.<br>
<br>
 Violent Harvest reserves the right to claim one item on a raid, IF it is stated in the signup post. <br>
<br>
9) Once you win something from a category (armor, Breastplate, Weapon, spell), you are to sit out of the next rolls until everyone in your class has won an item from that category as well.<br>
<br>
10) For items where four or more people are rolling for an item, the number zero will be added to the roll. If the zero is rolled, the Raid Leader will award the item to the person of their choosing. Winning an item by award of this type will not change rule number 9. After being awarded an item in a category you must sit out from all rolls in that category until each member of your class has won an item.<br>
<br>
11) If there is an argument or a unique situation arises that it is not covered in the rules stated, the Raid leader has final say on the decision regarding the piece in question.<br>
